            <title>[SPARK-31254] `HiveResult.toHiveString` does not use the current session time zone</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-31254</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, date/timestamp formatters in `HiveResult.toHiveString` are initialized once on instantiation of the `HiveResult` object, and pick up the session time zone. If the sessions time zone is changed, the formatters still use the previous one.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See the discussion there &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/23391#discussion_r397347820&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/23391#discussion_r397347820&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
